The paper focuses on compression algorithms, which are commonly used in data storage and retrieval tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithms on public datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithms in terms of compression ratios and decoding speeds, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
